Writers need to go back to writing (relatively) short stories, or short premises, instead or along with their bigger stories.

Examples
>misty morning / rainy day
>touch of grace
>of sliime and steel
>do I need a friend or just a lover or some shit by strong
>firebrand
>wolf smooching
>100 pages till I loves

It doesn't mean they need to be updated all at once, but be mostly planned out and their to entertain ideas that you may want to elaborate on at a further date.

A completed premises or an easy to digest one creates more discussion. Hell even with longer stories, writers need to add minor payoffs instead of relying on the big one at the climax.
